Date: Sun, 17 Oct 1999 22:52:40 -0700
From: DJR <djr@onlinemac.com>

I fail to see how Dr. Classen's holding of patents is relevant. Does that
negate the fact he is engaging in ongoing research? I cannot see that he
would have anything to gain. I also find it interesting that while Dr.
Grabenstein offers many citations to discredit Classen's findings, he
offers no data for the survey conducted by (I assume) the U.S. military
(re: "1500 lab workers at Fort Detrick, Maryland, vaccinated against
anthrax OR OTHER DANGEROUS INFECTIONS and followed for MANY YEARS")(caps
added).
Obviously, the organization administering the vaccine would have a
tremendous liability to those receiving it, should Dr. Classen be correct,
especially if they made it mandatory.
--
David J. Rogers
Director, Wilderness Medical Consultants
e-mail: djr@onlinemac.com
