[2
Date: Mon, 25 Oct 1999 07:57:23 -0400
From: Grabenstein, John D LTC <John.Grabenstein@otsg.amedd.army.mil>

Dr. Classen is welcome to patent his intellectual property. I mentioned the
patents to describe his previous assertions that anthrax vaccination could
be valuable to infants.
The manuscript reporting the health of the 1,500 laboratory workers at Fort
Detrick is being finalized now. This manuscript picks up where the third in
a series of reports left off (White CS III, Adler WH, McGann VG. Repeated
immunization: Possible adverse effects: Reevaluation of human subjects at
25 years. Annals of Internal Medicine 1974;81:594-600). The vaccinations
against other dangerous infections included various combinations of
anthrax, botulism, brucellosis, plague, Q fever, Rift Valley fever,
tularemia, Venezuelan equine encephalitis, and other vaccines. It is not
unusual for these 1500 workers to have received multiple vaccinations over
the span of 10 or 20 years or more. The medical surveillance of their
health has become
increasingly sophisticated over the years, to monitor the safety of the
vaccines they receive.
--
LTC John D. Grabenstein, RPh, PhD
Anthrax Vaccine Immunization Program
U.S. Army Medical Command
Falls Church, VA 22041-3258
http://www.anthrax.osd.mil
e-mail: John.Grabenstein@otsg.amedd.army.mil
